humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The N stage for a cancer patient is determined by the involvement of lymph nodes. In this report, it is stated that there are four lymph nodes positive for tumor by H&E (two in the right sentinel node and one in the non-sentinel node in the right axilla) out of a total of four lymph nodes examined. Therefore, the N stage for this patient is N2.
